v{{version}} - {{description}}

Usage: {{name}} <key> [options]

Key:
    the key to lookup in the package.json

Options: 

-h, --help     print this help message
-f, --file     provide the path to the package.json (default ./package.json)
-c, --count    count the number of keys in object or elements in an array
-d, --delete   delete the key from objects or a value from arrays
-s, --set      set the string value and create it if it doesn't exist
    --set-number
    --set-string
    --set-boolean
    --set-null
-r, --rename   updates a key and copies its values over (only if it exists)
-u, --update   update the value only if it exists
    --update-number
    --update-string
    --update-boolean
    --update-null
-a, --append   appends an element to an array value (eg. authors)
-e, --has      checks if a key exists
-q, --silent   don't show any error message (the exit code will still be non-zero)
-i, --is       checks if the value at the path is equal to a value provided
-t, --typeof   checks if the value at the path is of the provided type
--dep          list all the dependencies of any type (dev, peer, bundle...)
--dep=prod     list all the production dependencies ("dependencies")
--dep=dev      list all dev dependencies
--dep=peer     list all peer dependencies
--dep=opt      list all optional dependencies
--dep=bun      list all bundle dependencies
--query        list all keys that match a query
-v, --version  print the version information for pk
